de.lessvoid.nifty.node

Class AbsoluteLayoutChildNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lessvoid.nifty.node.AbsoluteLayoutChildNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NiftyNode

    public final class AbsoluteLayoutChildNode
extends Object
implements NiftyNode
    This is a child layout node for the AbsoluteLayoutNode. This node allows to set the x and y coordinate where the node is placed. Aside from the additional information applied, acts in the same way as a SimpleLayoutNode. So it just arranges any child item to it's full available size. The size this node requests will match the maximum height and width of all child nodes.
    Author:
    Martin Karing <nitram@illarion.org>
    See Also:
    for additional documentation
